2. Docker Fundamentals

Docker is a platform that packages:

Application code
Dependencies
Runtime

into a portable unit called a container.

Why Docker matters

Consistent environments across systems
Fast deployments
Lightweight compared to VMs
Ideal for microservices architecture

Containers are isolated environments with their own:

Network
Process space
Filesystem
Resource limits

An image is a template used to create containers.

Example command

