9. CMD vs ENTRYPOINT

These instructions define what runs when a container starts.

ENTRYPOINT defines the main command.
CMD defines default arguments.

Concept

ENTRYPOINT = executable
CMD = parameters

Example Dockerfile

FROM ubuntu
ENTRYPOINT ["sleep"]
CMD ["5"]

Run container

docker run myimage

Result

sleep 5

Override CMD

docker run myimage 10

Override ENTRYPOINT

docker run --entrypoint bash myimage

Best practice

Use ENTRYPOINT for the main application
Use CMD for configuration defaults

